<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;">This section provides steps integrate Cloud Optimizer (CO) 3.03 and containerized OpsBridge Manager (OBM) that is part of OpsB 2018.11 suite.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;"><span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">Step 1: Import the CO Management Pack package into OBM</span></p><ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Log on to the CO user interface in any of the supported browser and navigate to&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">Settings &gt; Integration</span>.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Scroll down and click&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">Download ZIP Package (OMi)</span>&nbsp;to download the OBM package:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OpsB_2018.05_1.jpg" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OpsB 2018.05 1.jpg" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/e/e0/OpsB_2018.05_1.jpg" width="306" height="105" data-file-width="306" data-file-height="105" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Prepare the package for upload.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Extract the downloaded file to the path shown below. Copy the file&nbsp;<i style="box-sizing: border-box;">OMi_Integration_Pack_for_vPV.zip</i>&nbsp;into the&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">OMi pod</span>.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/File:OpsB_2018.05_2.jpg" class="image" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;"><img alt="OpsB 2018.05 2.jpg" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/2/24/OpsB_2018.05_2.jpg" width="470" height="133" data-file-width="470" data-file-height="133" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: none; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></a><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Copy this file into a temp location on OBM box using any file-copy tool (like FileZilla or WinSCP) over ssh. Verify that the file exists after copying it in the temp location.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Copy the file to the OMi pod (assuming the zip file was copied to /tmp):<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">kubectl cp /tmp/OMi_Integration_Pack_for_vPV.zip opsbridge1/omi-0:/tmp/OMi_Integration_Pack_for_vPV.zip -c omi</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Verify that the file is on pod’s /tmp directory:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">kubectl exec omi-0 -c omi -n opsbridge1 ls /tmp</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Connect to the OBM's pod command line:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">kubectl exec omi-0 -c omi -n opsbridge1 bash –ti</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Navigate to /tmp:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">cd /tmp</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Unzip the package:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">unzip *vPV*</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Navigate to the folder – twice (there are 2 levels of vPV_OMi_Integration folders)<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">cd vPV_OMi_Integration</code><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">cd vPV_OMi_Integration</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Run the installer:<br style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">./vPV_integration_install.sh -i</code></li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Once the installation is complete, verify that the package was installed successfully on OBM by navigating to&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">Administration &gt; RTSM Administration &gt; Administration &gt; Package Manager</span>&nbsp;and verifying for HPOprvPV package in the list.</li></ol><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;"><span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">Step 2: Install the Operations Agent (OA) in CO system and activate it with OBM as monitored node</span></p><ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">See the&nbsp;<a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://softwaresupport.softwaregrp.com/km/KM323488" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;">Support Matrices</a>&nbsp;for Cloud Optimizer to know the supported OA versions.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Download the OA installer. See the&nbsp;<a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itomw/Operations_Agent:12.05/install_guide/_HPc_NewTopic" title="Operations Agent:12.05/install guide/ HPc NewTopic" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(58, 131, 230); background: none transparent;">OA Installation Documentation</a>&nbsp;for the instructions on downloading and installing OA and activating the system with OBM.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">After activating the OA installed system with OBM, make sure that on running the&nbsp;<i style="box-sizing: border-box;">ovc</i>&nbsp;command, all the agent processes are in RUNNING state.</li></ol><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;"><span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">Step 3: Deploy Management Aspects/Templates to the CO system and start monitoring</span></p><ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 3.2em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: none; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Log on to OBM user interface and navigate to&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">Administration &gt; Monitoring &gt; Management templates and Aspects &gt; vPV Management Pack</span>.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.65em; list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 0.65em;">Deploy&nbsp;<i style="box-sizing: border-box;">vPV Monitor</i>&nbsp;Management Pack on CO.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;">While deploying, in the&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">Parameter Summary</span>&nbsp;section, you may set the parameter&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;">Alarm Flag</span>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; color: rgb(232, 62, 140); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); border-radius: 2px; font-size: 13.125px; word-break: break-word; padding: 2px 5px !important;">true</code>&nbsp;for CO to forward VCenter alarms and events.</li></ol><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: normal;">The Containerized OBM and CO are integrated.</p>